-- UBS Hires Amram, Roberts Leaves Canadian Imperial, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-09-20T18:44:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-20/ubs-hires-amram-roberts-leaves-canadian-imperial-vlaad-says.html
Emmanuel Amram will join UBS AG’s
investment banking team in  Montreal  as associate director from
Bank of Montreal, according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based
financial services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * Don Roberts left Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce to start
up Nawitka Capital Advisors Ltd.  * Adam Adamou joined Euro Pacific Canada Inc. as an investment
banking managing director, focusing on technology and
innovation. Adamou recently served as chief executive officer of
Transitive Digital Media Corp.  * Michael Conrad joined Canada Pension Plan Investment Board in
its infrastructure group from Credit Suisse Group AG where he
was an investment banking analyst.  * Morguard Financial Corp. hired Albert Tzurkov as an assistant
portfolio manager from Thornmark Asset Management Inc.  * Former AltaCorp Capital Inc. employee Jared Coulson joined the
Desjardins Securities Inc.’s research team as an oil and gas
associate.  * Casimir Capital Ltd. hired Dwayne Sorobey in Calgary from Blue
Fish Capital Ventures.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
 edmitrieva1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
